-- Select objects with high probability of being YSO and exhibiting periodicity with specified criteria
WITH yso_prob AS (
    SELECT
        p.oid,
        p.probability AS possibility,
        p.class_name,
        p.ranking,
        f.name AS feature_name,
        f.value,
        f.fid AS filter_id,
        f.version AS feature_version
    FROM
        probability p
    JOIN
        feature f ON p.oid = f.oid
    WHERE
        p.class_name = 'YSO'
        AND p.probability > 0.7
        AND p.classifier_name IN ('lc_classifier', 'lc_classifier_top', 'lc_classifier_transient', 'lc_classifier_stochastic', 'lc_classifier_periodic')
        AND p.ranking = 1
        AND f.name = 'Period_band'
        AND f.value BETWEEN 3 AND 10
        AND EXISTS (
            SELECT 1
            FROM feature f2
            WHERE
                f2.oid = p.oid
                AND f2.name = 'Amplitude'
                AND f2.value > 0.5
        )
)
SELECT
    oid,
    possibility,
    class_name,
    feature_name,
    value,
    filter_id,
    feature_version
FROM
    yso_prob
ORDER BY
    possibility DESC;

-- Select relevant information for objects classified as SN II with specified conditions
WITH sn_ii_objects AS (
    SELECT o.oid, p.oid, p.class_name, p.probability, p.ranking
    FROM object o
    JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
    WHERE p.class_name = 'SNII'
      AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
      AND p.probability > 0.6
      AND p.ranking = 1
      AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN 2458600 AND 2459580 -- Corresponds roughly to 2019-2022
),
sn_ii_candidates AS (
    SELECT d.candid, d.oid, d.mjd, d.ra, d.dec, d.magpsf, d.sigmapsf, d.fid
    FROM detection d
    JOIN sn_ii_objects s ON d.oid = s.oid
    WHERE d.mjd BETWEEN 2458600 AND 2459580
),
mag_stats AS (
    SELECT ms.oid, ms.fid, ms.magmax, ms.magmax_corr, ms.dm_first, ms.dmdt_first
    FROM magstat ms
    WHERE ms.oid IN (SELECT oid FROM sn_ii_objects)
),
rise_rates AS (
    SELECT
        s.oid,
        -- Calculate initial rise rate as mag change over time in days
        CASE WHEN COUNT(*) > 1 THEN
            (MAX(ms.magmax) - MIN(ms.magmax)) / NULLIF(MAX(d.mjd) - MIN(d.mjd), 0)
        ELSE NULL END AS initial_rise_rate
    FROM sn_ii_candidates d
    JOIN magstat ms ON d.oid = ms.oid
    WHERE ms.fid IN (1, 2) -- g and r bands
    GROUP BY s.oid
),
detection_counts AS (
    SELECT oid, COUNT(*) AS ndet
    FROM detection
    GROUP BY oid
)
SELECT
    o.oid,
    c.candid,
    m.magmax,
    m.sigmapsf,
    m.dm_first,
    c.fid
FROM sn_ii_objects o
JOIN sn_ii_candidates c ON o.oid = c.oid
JOIN magstat m ON o.oid = m.oid AND m.fid = c.fid
JOIN rise_rates r ON o.oid = r.oid
JOIN detection_counts d ON o.oid = d.oid
WHERE
    r.initial_rise_rate > 0.5
    AND d.ndet > 50
    AND c.mjd BETWEEN 2458600 AND 2459580;
```

-- Select relevant information for objects classified as SN II with specified conditions
WITH sn_ii_objects AS (
    SELECT o.oid
    FROM object o
    JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
    WHERE p.class_name = 'SNIII'
      AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
      AND p.probability > 0.6
      AND p.ranking = 1
      AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN '2019-01-01' AND '2022-12-31'
      AND o.ndet > 50
),
rise_rates AS (
    SELECT
        m.oid,
        -- Calculate initial rise rate as change in magnitude over time between first and second detection
        (m.magfirst - m.maglast) / NULLIF((m.lastmjd - m.firstmjd), 0) AS rise_rate
    FROM magstat m
    WHERE m.ndet >= 2
)
SELECT
    d.oid,
    d.candid,
    d.magpsf,
    d.sigmapsf,
    -- Estimate initial rise as the difference between first and last magnitude divided by time
    (m.magfirst - m.maglast) / NULLIF((m.lastmjd - m.firstmjd), 0) AS initial_rise,
    d.fid
FROM detection d
JOIN sn_ii_objects s ON d.oid = s.oid
JOIN magstat m ON d.oid = m.oid AND d.mjd BETWEEN '2019-01-01' AND '2022-12-31' AND m.ndet > 0
WHERE
    -- Filter for g-band (fid=1) and r-band (fid=2)
    d.fid IN (1, 2)
    AND -- Calculate rise rate for each band
    (
        -- For g-band
        (d.fid = 1 AND 
         (SELECT (magfirst - maglast) / NULLIF((lastmjd - firstmjd), 0) FROM magstat WHERE oid = d.oid AND fid = 1) > 0.5)
        OR
        -- For r-band
        (d.fid = 2 AND 
         (SELECT (magfirst - maglast) / NULLIF((lastmjd - firstmjd), 0) FROM magstat WHERE oid = d.oid AND fid = 2) > 0.5)
    )
ORDER BY d.mjd;

-- Select specified columns for objects with given ZTF identifiers, filtering for g band (fid=2) and zero dubious corrections
SELECT 
    o.oid AS "ZTF identifier",
    m.ndet AS "number of detections",
    m.dmdt_first AS "initial rise estimate",
    m.dm_first AS "first difference magnitude"
FROM 
    object o
JOIN 
    magstat m ON o.oid = m.oid
WHERE 
    o.oid IN ('ZTF20adadshh', 'ZTF21aaabvit', 'ZTF21aaabvjk')
    AND m.fid = 2
    AND m.ndubious = 0;
```

```sql
-- Select up to 50 objects with specified classification probabilities
SELECT 
    o.oid AS ztf_id,
    p_stamp.probability AS prob_stamp_agn,
    p_lc.probability AS prob_lc_lpv
FROM 
    object o
-- Subquery to get the most probable AGN classification from stamp_classifier_1.0.4
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        p.oid,
        p.probability
    FROM 
        probability p
    WHERE 
        p.class_name = 'AGN'
        AND p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
        AND p.ranking = 1
        AND p.probability > 0.6
) p_stamp ON o.oid = p_stamp.oid
-- Subquery to get the most probable LPV classification from lc_classifier
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        p.oid,
        p.probability
    FROM 
        probability p
    WHERE 
        p.class_name = 'LPV'
        AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
        AND p.ranking = 1
        AND p.probability > 0.7
) p_lc ON o.oid = p_lc.oid
-- Limit the result to 50 objects
LIMIT 50;
```

-- Select up to 50 objects with specified classification probabilities
SELECT 
    o.oid AS ztf_id,
    p_stamp.probability AS prob_stamp_agn,
    p_lc.probability AS prob_lc_lpv
FROM 
    object o
-- Subquery to get the most probable AGN classification from stamp_classifier_1.0.4
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        p1.oid,
        p1.probability
    FROM 
        probability p1
    WHERE 
        p1.class_name = 'AGN'
        AND p1.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
        AND p1.classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
        AND p1.ranking = 1
) p_stamp ON o.oid = p_stamp.oid
-- Subquery to get the most probable LPV classification from lc_classifier
JOIN (

        p2.oid,
